This paper deals with unsupervised domain adaptation using generative models and self-ensembling. The main focus is on image datasets, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also involves deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves image processing and manipulation, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves training models using generated data, which is a common technique in neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
